                <h1>When Did UGGs Come Out? History & Popularity Explained</h1>
                <p>UGGs, originally designed in the 1960s, gained significant popularity in the 2000s. They were introduced to the mainstream fashion scene when celebrities began wearing them, leading to a global trend. Their unique design, featuring sheepskin and a cozy appeal, made them a must-have item, especially during colder seasons.</p>
